<h2>Why Sleep Onset Latency Matters More Than You Think</h2>
<p>The average person takes 10-20 minutes to fall asleep. But if you're struggling with racing thoughts, stress, or sleep anxiety, that number jumps to 30+ minutes. Even a small reduction in time-to-sleep adds up: a 5-minute improvement means 30 extra minutes of sleep per week. Pillow sprays work by creating a consistent sensory anchor that tells your nervous system it's safe to transition to sleep.</p>
